    {
      "title": "The Shortened Noun (الاسم المقصور)",
      "titleArabic": "الاسم المقصور",
      "content": [
        "The shortened noun (الاسم المقصور) ends in alif maqsura (ى or ا). Case endings are estimated (مقدرة) and not pronounced.",
        "Examples include فَتَى (young man), هُدَى (guidance), and مُصْطَفَى (chosen one)."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Ends in ى or ا (alif maqsura)",
        "Case endings are estimated due to the alif",
        "In dual: الفَتَيَانِ، الفَتَيَيْنِ",
        "In plural: فَتَيَات or الفَتَوْنَ (rare)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "فَتَى", "english": "young man" },
        { "arabic": "هُدَى", "english": "guidance" },
        { "arabic": "مُسْتَشْفَى", "english": "hospital" },
        { "arabic": "مَعْنَى", "english": "meaning" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "The Defective Noun (الاسم المنقوص)",
      "titleArabic": "الاسم المنقوص",
      "content": [
        "The defective noun (الاسم المنقوص) ends in ya preceded by kasra (ـِي). The nominative and genitive case markers are estimated.",
        "In indefinite form, the ya is usually dropped in nominative and genitive: قَاضٍ (a judge)."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Ends in ـِي (ya preceded by kasra)",
        "Nominative & genitive are estimated: قَاضٍ، قَاضٍ",
        "Accusative is visible: قَاضِيًا",
        "Definite form keeps the ya: الْقَاضِي"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "قَاضٍ / الْقَاضِي", "english": "judge" },
        { "arabic": "مُحَامٍ / الْمُحَامِي", "english": "lawyer" },
        { "arabic": "دَاعٍ / الدَّاعِي", "english": "caller / preacher" },
        { "arabic": "سَاعٍ / السَّاعِي", "english": "messenger / seeker" }
      ]
    }
  ],
